OL,3,CPrince George turns 13 in new birthday
OL,4,Cportrait as he prepares to start Eton
OL,6,FGeorge will also become a boarder
OL,7,Fwhile studying there, as the school
OL,8,Fhas 25 boarding houses, each of which
OL,9,Fhas approximately 55 pupils.
OL,11,FHe previously attended Lambrook
OL,12,FSchool, a private co-ed prep school in
OL,13,FBerkshire, where he occasionally
OL,14,Fboarded to prepare for Eton.
OL,16,FTwenty prime ministers have attended
OL,17,FEton, including most recently David
OL,18,FCameron and Boris Johnson.
